		<div class="post-680 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-copywrong category-free-culture category-freedom category-law category-politics" id="post-680">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2009/09/22/public-knowledge/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Public Knowledge">Public Knowledge</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Here&#8217;s a rather feisty and spirited interview I did with Art Brodsky of <a href="http://www.publicknowledge.org/" target="_blank">Public Knowledge</a>, a &#8220;D.C.-based public interest group working to defend citizens&#8217; rights in the emerging digital culture.&#8221; It&#8217;s very low-res and gritty Skype video, but the message comes through loud and clear.</p>
